2 exercises to do with battle ropes and a KB to engage that core and upper body!
 
•First one, tie the KB to the end of the battle rope, get into a plank position and pull with one arm until the KB reaches the end point, you will have to pull it back and then switch to the other side, do this 5 times each side!

•Second, set up will be the same but this time sit down, brace your core and pull with both hands do this 10 times through

Are you a shake shack lover like me and Nathan? Try making them at home next time! Super easy! 

Sauce:
1/4 cup mayo
1 tablespoon Dijon mustard 
1 tablespoon ketchup 
1 teaspoon pickle juice 

Instructions:
-make the sauce with the recipe above!
-spread the butter on the buns and facing down put on pan medium heat, remove once melted and golden brown
-divide the beef into 4 Pattie’s and place on medium heat
-flatten down and cook til edges are nice and crispy!
-put the sauce on the buns and add the Pattie’s and any toppings. My go to is tomato, lettuce, onion and pickles 

Enjoy!!!

The primary difference between a single-leg press and a double-leg press lies in the number of legs used during the exercise. In a single-leg press, you work one leg at a time, which can help address muscle imbalances and activate stabilizing muscles more intensely. On the other hand, a double-leg press involves both legs simultaneously, providing overall leg strength and targeting larger muscle groups. The choice between them depends on your fitness goals and individual preferences.
